      "role": "user",
      "content": "okay but if you look at the \"mainstream\" views, doesn't it seem like the argument for tariffs is mostly just an exception to the rule? like isn't the standard economic reality that tariffs are pretty much always a net negative for the economy? it feels like you're giving equal weight to both, but is one actually just wrong most of the time?",
